text:
My fondest and most memorable moment with my father was while serving my national service. Throughout the 2 years, regardless of my postings and time of book out, he would always try his best to pick me up so that I won't have to travel home with all my heavy bags. On the weekends, he would also arrange simple family outings to restaurants so that I can have some nice food. He would then bring me to the supermarket to get some necessities like biscuits and vitamin C that I can bring to camp so I can stay full and healthy. After this, he will drive and send me back to camp. The cycle consistently repeats itself and before I know it, 2 years just passed like that.
Perhaps, the fondest memory I have of him is not an episodic event but an accumulation of love and dedicated efforts overtime. I would like to thank my dad for his love throughout the years. Happy Father's Day! :D

